commitResults.messageTitle: Add PolicyType list panel and card UI components
commitResults.messageBody: Introduces PolicyTypeListPanel and PolicyTypeCard classes to display policy types in the UI. Updates MainWindow to support switching between client and policy views, and modifies FXML files to accommodate the new panel and card layouts.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor to use InsuraBook as main data model
commitResults.messageBody: Replaces AddressBook with InsuraBook throughout the application, updating storage, model, logic, and parser components. Adds InsuraBook-specific storage classes and JSON serialization, updates user preferences, and adapts tests and utility classes to use InsuraBook. This refactor prepares the codebase for handling policy types and clients under the new InsuraBook model.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add sample policy types and InsuraBook data util
commitResults.messageBody: Introduced methods to generate sample PolicyType objects and a sample InsuraBook instance with clients and policy types for testing or demonstration purposes. Also added necessary imports and updated method names to reflect the new data model.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add methods to set policy types in UniquePolicyTypeList
commitResults.messageBody: Introduced setPolicyTypes methods to allow replacing the contents of UniquePolicyTypeList with another UniquePolicyTypeList or a List of PolicyType. This enhances flexibility for managing the list's contents.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor tests to use InsuraBook instead of AddressBook
commitResults.messageBody: Replaces all references to AddressBook with InsuraBook in test files, including model, storage, and utility classes. Updates method and variable names to match the new InsuraBook naming convention. Adds InsuraBookBuilder and InsuraBookTest, removes AddressBookBuilder and AddressBookTest. Also adds InsuraBookParserTest for parser coverage.

commitResults.messageTitle: Prevent adding Policy that is not offered
commitResults.messageBody:
Issue:
Adding a Policy to the client with a policy type id that does not exist breaks the application. Should not be able to add a policy to a client that does not exist inside InsuraBook. Should not be able to set an expiration date before today's date.

Fixes:
Throws policy type not found if attempting to add a policy to a client when the policy type does not exist in the application.
Throws an exception if provided expiration date of policy is before todays date.
